Come out and cheer on our Lady Lions as they host LM in their home schedule opener tonight. We will celebrate our seniors and matches will start at 5:30 and will be broadcast live on the school YouTube Channel. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=izd77JaZa20

Fans should note the following spectator guidelines will be in place:

All athletes, coaches, and spectators should enter through the main lobby entrance at the front of the building off of Devoe Street.

Spectators are required to wear face coverings upon entering the building and are required to keep them on throughout the games. Please note that Johnson County is under a mask ordinance that we are required to follow.

Per IGHSAA guidelines, we encourage spectators to socially distance themselves from other spectators. Both the bottom and top deck will be available, but we encourage fans to use the top deck where more space is available.

Although our concessions stand will be open, we will only be selling drinks and candy/candy bars.

We are excited to announce that LTCSD will be part of this program! Starting September 10th, all students will receive FREE meals until December 31st, 2020 or until funding runs out, whichever comes first. For more information, please click on the provided link.

https://www.fns.usda.gov/news-item/usda-035520

Families do not need to fill out the Iowa Eligibility application to qualify for free meals during this program. When the program expires our normal meal charges will resume. We encourage families that wish to complete the application to do so now to prepare for the return of our normal meal charges.

Go Lions!

post_text:
Attention Parents and Students:
The Golden Circle College & Career Fair is Going Virtual!

The Golden Circle College & Career Fair is traditionally the largest in Iowa and has something to offer every student at every age. Whether you’re a freshman or sophomore just starting to explore careers, or a junior or senior narrowing your list of college choices, Golden Circle is the perfect opportunity for you to gather knowledge, make connections, and begin to make informed decisions about your future.

Students of every age have something to gain at Golden Circle. From learning about different career fields, to speaking with colleges, universities and career experts, there’s something for everyone. Register to attend and gain access to career planning and college information videos. Take part in the scavenger hunt and enter to win one of several VISA gift cards.
Visit www.ICANsucceed.org/goldencircle for all the event details and to register to attend. The fair is FREE and registration provides access to the event portal and additional planning information.

Go Lions!

shared_text:
Iowa FFA Association
August 10 at 7:34 PM ·

Congratulations to Allison Marshek for being our first Member Monday Spotlight. This next year she will be a senior serving as the Vice-President of the Lone Tree FFA Chapter. Over the years Allison has volunteered to help with the food bank, the test plot, safety day and several other events. Along with her work she has served on several committees and a committee chair. Allison earned her Iowa Degree last year and placed 3rd in the state for her proficiency area. She is always working hard to get more members involved and advance her chapter. Keep up the great work Allison!

Lone Tree Wellness Center
July 28 at 6:11 PM ·

FLOOR BURN ACADEMY! As you may have heard the men's Iowa basketball team has been quarantined, which means our guest coach Joe Wieskamp will be unable to attend Floor Burn Academy Camp this week. Join me in prayers and sending good mojo to Joe and everyone affected. What does this mean for our camp! WE ARE ON! We have a fabulous staff on board and we are moving forward as planned! I am working on arranging a meet and greet with Joe W. at a later date for all players who attend our camp this week. I will keep you posted when we get a date set up! Attitude is everything :) Be safe, be happy.

post_text:
Congratulations to our Lady Lions with their win over the Highland Huskies to advance to the next round of postseason play! The Lady Lions will play Friday, July 17, in Lisbon. Fans, please note the following:

•There will be no bleacher seating available at the stadium. Please bring lawn chairs or be prepared to stand.
•The area marked off by caution tape if for players. Please stay out of this space.
•For the health and safety of our admission workers, please encourage spectators to bring exact change for their party.
•Social distancing between family groups is an expectation. Please be respectful of other family's space.
•Please do not touch foul balls. The fielding team will be responsible for this.
•After the game is over, fans should not enter the field of play.
•No concessions will be available.

Go Lions!

post_text: To the Class of 2020: This article following Lone Tree graduate (1983) Steve Forbes could not have come at a better time. After reading, we hope that you take this single statement with you ... "take Lone Tree with you". This small town is in your corner. This small town has provided you with the opportunity to grow and now it is your turn to take the best of Lone Tree with you and sprinkle our small town work ethic and kindness everywhere you go. Don't ever forget....Once a Lion, Always a Lion.

post_text: Once a Lion, Always a Lion! #WeBleedBlack&Gold
shared_text:
Steven Forbes
May 4 at 5:41 AM ·

At my press conference this past Friday, when I was named the Head Basketball Coach at Wake Forest University, I made the following comment to the media & the Wake Forest fans, "I went to school in Lone Tree, Iowa from 1970 to 1983. Our school colors were BLACK & GOLD. If you cut my veins, I bleed BLACK & GOLD! I have now come full circle from Lone Tree to Wake Forest!! Excited to start this new journey! #LTLions

post_text: Do you know how hard it was to find a picture of these two!?! Today is National Principal’s Day and we have two of the best. They are not here for the limelight but work tirelessly, behind the scenes, to ensure that every student has a success story to tell and every teacher knows that they are their “cornerman”. They understand that their success shines the brightest when the spotlight is directed on our students and staff. We are very lucky to have these two leading the elementary and MSHS. Join me in wishing Mr. Stone and Mrs. Jacque a very happy National Principal’s Day! Here’s to low quality photos and high quality principals! Go Lions!

ICAN Q&A on Facebook Live

An ICAN team member will go live at 2pm Monday through Thursday on the ICAN Facebook page to discuss important planning topics and answer questions from students, parents, and school counselors.
Next weeks' topics include:
• Monday: Job Shadows and Internship
• Tuesday: Four Year Plans
• Wednesday: FAFSA Day - All about FAFSA with speakers from ICAN, Iowa Association of Independent Colleges and Universities and Iowa College Aid
• Thursday: AP vs Dual Enrollment Courses
Follow our Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/ICANsucceed/
And join our online conversations. This is a great way to keep students engaged with short spurts of information. We hope to see you there!

post_text:
Class of 2021, as we continue to work through these strange times, I want to ensure you continue looking forward and make plans for your future. With that in mind, now is the time to begin transitioning current juniors into the mindset of senior year. These ICAN Senior Alerts are tailored to each class, and send out timely reminders of specific steps in the process for senior year. Alerts include application deadline reminders, important steps in the process, scholarship announcements, and events specific to seniors to help them success their senior year and successfully transition into their next steps be it college, an apprenticeship, or career. Senior alerts begin in August.

I’d like to encourage the class of 2021 and parents to sign up using the ICAN link https://www.icansucceed.org/about-ican/services/the-resource-zone/e-alerts-tips-signup

Update on School Closure - April 3, 2020

On Thursday, April 2, Governor Reynolds extended the closure of Iowa schools through April 30, 2020. This affects all school programming including activities as well as extra-curricular practices and competitions.

Our administration team will meet this morning to discuss how the LTCSD will proceed in providing our students with educational services. Information will be released detailing these services in the near future.

In the meantime, stay home and stay healthy!

Lone Tree FFA
March 20 at 1:55 AM ·

This year, the LT FFA Officer Team filled out the National Chapter Award Application and earned 13th in the State! On to Nationals!

The National Chapter Award Program is designed to recognize FFA chapters that actively implement the mission and strategies of the organization. These chapters improve chapter operations using the National Quality Chapter Standards (NQCS) and a Program of Activities (POA) that emphasize growing leaders, building communities and strengthening agriculture. Chapters are rewarded for providing educational experiences for the entire membership.

Upon state approval, LTCSD will be offering free curbside meal kit pickup for ALL students from 4:30-6:00pm Monday's AND Thursday's starting March 23rd until school resumes. Pick up location will be the school parking lot outside of the Library doors. Attached is a sign-up sheet that should be completed prior to pick-up so that we can ensure that we have enough free meal kits for all. Please note, children receiving free meal kits will need to be with the parents at the time of pick up per state law, however, the children are also allowed to pick up lunches without an adult as long as their contact is on our list. If you have any trouble submitting your responses you may call the office from 9AM-11AM at (319) 629-4212 to have your name added to the list.

Proud Lion Fan Alert! Monday night we celebrated our new inductees as well as our graduating National Honor Society members. These students represent the best of Lone Tree through their Scholarship, Service, Leadership and Character. They volunteer hours of service to our community and school on top of the hours of study to achieve the high standards of scholarship to qualify for and NHS nomination. We congratulate our 14 graduating seniors and welcome 13 inductees to this elite Lion Society of NHS! Go Lions!

A special congratulations to Mrs. Sharon Murry as she was recognized as an Honorary Member by our members.

post_text: Proud Lion Alert! Ashley Yedlik was selected by Lone Tree Community School to attend the Hugh O’Brian Youth Leadership (HOBY) conference in June of 2019 at Drake University. For more than five decades, HOBY has inspired young people to make a difference and become catalysts for positive change in their home, school, workplace, and community. As America’s foremost youth leadership organization, HOBY has a long history of successfully motivating young people to develop into outstanding leaders. Yedlik was named South Regional Champion She is in charge of the entire Southern part of Iowa. She was just recently named a JUFA (Junior Facilitator) and will be a group leader during the HOBY conference that will be in June. Great things are happening to our students because great things are happening at Lone Tree! Go Lions!

post_text:
On Friday, 6-12 grade students took part in a LION TRAINING lesson on the topic of Healthy Relationships. Our goal was to help students understand characteristics of healthy and unhealthy relationships and demonstrate effective strategies to avoid or end an unhealthy relationships, and know how to effectively communicate personal boundaries while respecting the boundaries of others. Parents and Guardians, join us in our efforts-

post_text: Mr. Postman can you see 🎶 if there’s a letter for me? 🎶 What a great experience for our Preschoolers as they listened to Mrs. Wollrab about her time with the Lone Tree Post Office and received their own pieces of mail. They then walked to the Post Office to mail their own letters! We love Lone Tree and our community members! Go Lions!

post_text: Our elementary students got to meet Irish, Mrs. Bryce’s dog, on Friday. Irish was visiting the school to provide some doggie therapy to our students during the Self Care/Stress Relief Day. I would say she was a hit with the kids! Great things are happening at Lone Tree! Go Lions!

post_text: Friday was another great Self-Care/Stress Relief Day for our MSHS students. This annual event has become a highlight of the week for our students as we celebrate National School Counselor's week with our very own Mrs. Bryce! Great things are happening at Lone Tree!

Lone Tree Athletic Boosters
February 8 at 3:38 PM ·

Strength and Conditioning Showcase packets were handed out at the assembly Friday. Parents please make sure your student-athlete brings theirs home and completes their donation requests. This takes very little effort and reaps great rewards for our athletic programs. Packets are due back by February 22nd. Thank you!

post_text: Congratulations to Chloe Mills, who was our Student of the Week this week! Chloe was nominated for her strong work in the classroom and for always being willing to lend a hand to those in need of help in the classroom. Great job, Chloe! Keep up the great work!

Macie Bopp - Job Interview
